    <name>
      <text>Finding Inverses of a linear Functions</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find  the inverse of the function below</p>
<p>\( \displaystyle f(x)={@func@}\)</p>
<p><b>Note:</b> \(\ln\) can be typed as <code> log</code></p>
<p>Leave your answer in exact form</p>
<p>\(f^{-1}(x)=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>\(\begin{align}
\displaystyle f(x)&={@func@}\\
y&={@func@}\\
&{@sol2@}\\
&{@sol3@}\\
&{@sol4@}\\
\end{align}\)</p>
<p>Swap \(x\) and \(y\) to write the inverse function</p>
<p>\(f^{-1}(x)= \displaystyle{@ta1@}\)</p>
<p></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
